Martin VANDERBURG, Defendant, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES, Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, First Circuit. October 17, 1929. No. 2354. A. Chesley York, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Boston, Mass. (John L. Gay, U. S. Atty., and Jesus A. Gonzalez, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of San Juan, Porto Rico, on the brief), for appellee.

Before BINGHAM, ANDERSON, and WILSON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the District Court is affirmed.
